## Phase Instructions

{{^skip_scout}}
### Phase 1 — Scout (skip only if you already know the exact files and changes needed)
```bash
grove task add scout-<topic> "Scout <topic>" --description "<what to find: file paths, patterns, interfaces>"
grove spawn scout-<topic> -n <name>-scout -c scout --parent {{agent_name}}
```
Wait for scout mail, then use its findings to write precise builder specs.

For multi-subsystem tasks, spawn parallel scouts:
```bash
grove spawn scout-backend -n backend-scout -c scout --parent {{agent_name}}
grove spawn scout-frontend -n frontend-scout -c scout --parent {{agent_name}}
```
